  "body": "### Description\r\nAs a node operator, I want helpful error messages so that I know how to fix things.\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n* When there is a port conflict on starting Teku I should get a nice explanatory message that\r\n   - Tells me the exact problem (it currently says \"Address already in use\", not \"Port already in use\")\r\n   - Specifies which port number\r\n   - Tells me to consult `--help`  if I want to change the port number\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\r\n1. Start Teku with `--p2p=N` where `N` is the number of a port already in use.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:** [What you expect to happen]\r\nA nice explanatory message.\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior:** [What actually happens]\r\n```\r\n18:43:14.177 ERROR - PLEASE FIX OR REPORT | Unexpected exception thrown for beaconchain-async-0 java.util.concurrent.CompletionException: java.net.BindException: Address already in use (See log file for full stack trace)\r\n```\r\nThis is unhelpful üòÉ The logs add no useful info.\r\n\r\n**Frequency:** [What percentage of the time does it occur?]\r\n100%\r\n\r\n### Versions (Add all that apply)\r\n* Software version: teku/v0.12.2-dev-43e04799/linux-x86_64/-ubuntu-openjdk64bitservervm-java-11\r\n* OS Name & Version: Ubuntu 19.10\r\n",
